result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley Rochelle Josephson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Ignition Interlock Device Tampering/Failure to Install, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 347.413(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: $550 bail applied. Remaining balance is $136. Court grants payment plan of $50 per month beginning April 1, 2017. Failure to pay will result in one day in jail for every $25 outstanding.

Defendant is granted Huber privileges for childcare and employment.
Court grants transfer request to Brown County Jail if both sheriff departments agree to transfer.
Defendant to submit DNA sample while in custody.
